Here’s a small extension to the layout you already have:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>After Quiet</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Gentium+Book+Basic&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
body {
  font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', serif;
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: #222;
  background: #fafafa;
  margin: 0;
}

/* one screen per section */
section {
  min-height: 100vh;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 0 8vw;
}

h2 { opacity: 0; animation: fadeIn 2s ease forwards; }
@keyframes fadeIn { from {opacity:0;} to {opacity:1;} }

blockquote.epigraph {
  font-style: italic;
  font-size: 0.9em;
  text-align: center;
  color: #555;
  margin: 60vh 0;
}

/* navigation links */
nav {
  position: fixed;
  top: 50%;
  width: 100%;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  pointer-events: none; /* keep invisible for scrolling */
}
nav a {
  pointer-events: auto;
  text-decoration: none;
  color: #777;
  padding: 0.5em 1em;
  font-size: 0.9em;
  opacity: 0.5;
  transition: opacity 0.3s;
}
nav a:hover {opacity: 0.9;}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<blockquote class="epigraph">Every silence teaches the shape of hearing.</blockquote>

<section id="one">
  <h2>I. Stillness</h2>
  <p>Before the light, the room is a shape without edges…</p>
</section>

<section id="two">
  <h2>II. First Notice</h2>
  <p>The click becomes a whisper of steam…</p>
</section>

<section id="three">
  <h2>III. Return</h2>
  <p>Steam edges from the kettle, rising in thin spirals…</p>
</section>

<nav>
  <a href="#one">◀ Prev</a>
  <a href="#three">Next ▶</a>
</nav>

</body>
</html>
```

Each navigation link jumps smoothly to its section when clicked, but it’s subtle enough not to distract; the half‑transparent text feels like part of the quiet design.

You can update the link targets (`#one`, `#two`, etc.) for the first and last sections or add small arrows styled with the font you’ve chosen.  

Would you like a variant where the “Prev / Next” anchors automatically hide at the first and last section so they don’t invite clicks beyond the book’s edges?
